article.headline: BYU 95, E. New Mexico 62
article.story: PROVO, Utah -- Tyler Haws scored 19 points and Brandon Davies added 17 points to lead BYU to a 95-62 win over Eastern New Mexico Tuesday night. The Cougars (8-3) also got 14 points and eight rebounds from Agustin Ambrosino, and Cory Calvert contributed 10 points. The Greyhounds, who play in Division II, led in the first minute of the game. BYU used a 16-2 run to pull away from an 11-all tie, and It was 44-29 at halftime. Rodney Blackmon led Eastern New Mexico (5-6) with 14 points.
